#
# 9/5/2020.
#
# This is a (so far) non-working experiment.  I read that there is an open source scanner 
# generator called "reflex" which is supposedly flex-compatible.  According to their website,
# this tool generates faster scanners that flex.   
#
# So far:  it can process the ExpressionLexer.l file w/o complaint. (gives 2 warnings)
#
# The *cxx file it produces appears to be much more "clean" than what comes out of flex.
#
# However, I was unable to get it to compile.  I think this had to do with all the weird
# hackish stuff I had to do to make flex/bison work with C++ and also with multiple parsers
# to avoid name conflicts.
#
#


